{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-tags-js","path":"/tag/til/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"author":{"name":"Tony Guo","url":"https://tonykwok.github.io"}}},"taxonomyYaml":{"id":"TIL","excerpt":"Learnings captured for educational purposes and posterity.","html":"<p>Learnings captured for educational purposes and posterity.</p>\n"},"allMarkdownRemark":{"edges":[{"node":{"id":"edd2fcf9-35e3-5ea1-81c3-be022c3446a8","excerpt":"<p>Slowly but surely, I’ve been chipping away at my site’s <a href=\"/notes/autumn-refresh/#build-and-deploy\">build time on <strong>Netlify</strong></a>.</p>\n<p>There’s little left for me to optimize until Jekyll drops some nice updates in <a href=\"https://github.com/jekyll/jekyll/projects/2\">version 4.0</a>. I’ve <a href=\"https://github.com/mmistakes/made-mistakes-jekyll/issues/629\">cached the rendering of Liquid includes</a>…</p>","timeToRead":2,"frontmatter":{"title":"Faster Netlify builds","date":"2019-02-26T00:00:00.000Z","date_pretty":"February 26th, 2019","date_from_now":"a year ago","path":"/notes/faster-netlify-builds/","author":null,"excerpt":null,"image":null}}},{"node":{"id":"d193a24c-d74c-5336-842a-a8aab26216e8","excerpt":"<p>While inspecting the markup of some syntax highlighted code blocks I noticed something I hadn’t before, <code class=\"language-text\">language-lexer</code> classes:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"html\"><pre class=\"language-html\"><code class=\"language-html\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>div</span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">class</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span>language-css highlighter-rouge<span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n  <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>pre</span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">class</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span>highlight<span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n    <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>code</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>.foo { color: red; }<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>code</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n  <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>pre</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>div</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span></code></pre></div>\n<p>This extra hook<sup id=\"fnref-1\"><a href=\"#fn-1\" class=\"footnote-ref\">1</a></sup> on the <code class=\"language-text\">&lt;div&gt;</code>…</p>","timeToRead":2,"frontmatter":{"title":"Styling language specific code blocks with Jekyll","date":"2017-05-16T00:00:00.000Z","date_pretty":"May 16th, 2017","date_from_now":"3 years ago","path":"/notes/styling-language-specific-code-blocks/","author":null,"excerpt":"Interesting styling possibilities with syntax highlighted code blocks.","image":null}}},{"node":{"id":"4e16e1b5-ca34-5ec1-b280-af39884ef7b7","excerpt":"<p>While investigating ways of using static files with Jekyll for a site prototype I was building, I learned that <code class=\"language-text\">site.static_files</code> was a thing. What is it and…</p>","timeToRead":4,"frontmatter":{"title":"Accessing static files in Jekyll","date":"2017-01-30T00:00:00.000Z","date_pretty":"January 30th, 2017","date_from_now":"3 years ago","path":"/notes/static-files/","author":null,"excerpt":null,"image":null}}},{"node":{"id":"4d64c183-7c43-51a0-a2ad-4f4662e404fc","excerpt":"<p>The question of how to write a list inside of a table cell with <a href=\"http://kramdown.gettalong.org/\"><strong>Kramdown</strong></a> recently came up in a thread on <a href=\"http://talk.jekyllrb.com/\">Jekyll Talk</a> — prompting me to look…</p>","timeToRead":2,"frontmatter":{"title":"HTML inside Kramdown table cells","date":"2016-11-08T00:00:00.000Z","date_pretty":"November 8th, 2016","date_from_now":"4 years ago","path":"/notes/kramdown-table-html/","author":null,"excerpt":null,"image":null}}},{"node":{"id":"f0c7d0a5-4b1a-5abc-a4fb-070a9d9d4ddb","excerpt":"<p>You know what sucks? Maintaining two separate branches of an open source project, just to host its source code and documentation together…</p>","timeToRead":1,"frontmatter":{"title":"Configuring publishing sources for GitHub Pages","date":"2016-11-04T00:00:00.000Z","date_pretty":"November 4th, 2016","date_from_now":"4 years ago","path":"/notes/github-pages-publishing-source/","author":null,"excerpt":null,"image":null}}},{"node":{"id":"7c8eeca3-ec45-5a5b-9bda-573404d68389","excerpt":"<p>Not to overstate the obvious here, but oil pastels do not behave like colored pencils.</p>\n<p>Their size and shape should have been enough to clue…</p>","timeToRead":1,"frontmatter":{"title":"Oil pastels are not pencils","date":"2016-10-27T00:00:00.000Z","date_pretty":"October 27th, 2016","date_from_now":"4 years ago","path":"/notes/oil-pastels/","author":null,"excerpt":"Not to overstate the obvious here, but oil pastels do not behave like colored pencils...","image":{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"aspectRatio":1.450381679389313,"src":"/static/5016d80474633fd8ed1f80aa09998ade/ad579/oil-pastel-sunset-finished.jpg","srcSet":"/static/5016d80474633fd8ed1f80aa09998ade/5827c/oil-pastel-sunset-finished.jpg 190w,\n/static/5016d80474633fd8ed1f80aa09998ade/a4187/oil-pastel-sunset-finished.jpg 380w,\n/static/5016d80474633fd8ed1f80aa09998ade/ad579/oil-pastel-sunset-finished.jpg 760w,\n/static/5016d80474633fd8ed1f80aa09998ade/d0063/oil-pastel-sunset-finished.jpg 1140w,\n/static/5016d80474633fd8ed1f80aa09998ade/fdaf9/oil-pastel-sunset-finished.jpg 1520w,\n/static/5016d80474633fd8ed1f80aa09998ade/9352a/oil-pastel-sunset-finished.jpg 1600w","sizes":"(max-width: 760px) 100vw, 760px"}}}}}},{"node":{"id":"a064052d-a333-591d-9a92-c8b127deae19","excerpt":"<p>Playing with the new <strong>Depth Effect</strong> (aka <a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/explore/tags/fauxkeh/\"><em>fauxkeh</em></a>) on my iPhone 7 Plus got me thinking about Gaussian blurs, and how to improve their use on…</p>","timeToRead":1,"frontmatter":{"title":"CSS blur effect","date":"2016-10-25T00:00:00.000Z","date_pretty":"October 25th, 2016","date_from_now":"4 years ago","path":"/notes/css-blur-effect/","author":null,"excerpt":null,"image":null}}},{"node":{"id":"900e8e48-ae13-52ba-a3c1-06ea2b8fc5ae","excerpt":"<p>In my never ending quest to micro-optimize the hell out of my site, I ran into a snag when trying to use <abbr title=\"Server Side Includes\">SSI</abbr> directives.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://github.com/mmistakes/made-mistakes-jekyll/tree/10.3.0\">Version 10.2</a> of this site was my half-baked attempt at <a href=\"/articles/using-jekyll-2016/#critical-path-css\">eliminating render-blocking CSS</a>…</p>","timeToRead":3,"frontmatter":{"title":"Using SSI to detect cookies","date":"2016-10-24T00:00:00.000Z","date_pretty":"October 24th, 2016","date_from_now":"4 years ago","path":"/notes/using-ssi/","author":null,"excerpt":"In my never ending quest to micro-optimize the hell out of my site, I ran into a snag when trying to use SSI directives to improve the loading of critical CSS and cached stylesheets.","image":null}}}]}},"pageContext":{"tag":"TIL","pageNumber":0,"humanPageNumber":1,"skip":0,"limit":10,"numberOfPages":1,"previousPagePath":"","nextPagePath":""}}}